    "body": "Boxlib has compile time knob for number of spatial dimensions.\r\n\r\nI am adding a variant to boxlib like so...\r\n\r\n    variant('dims', default=3, description='Number of spatial dimensions')\r\n\r\nOk, fine and good.\r\n\r\nBut, what is the syntax for having another package that depends on boxlib with dims set to 3?\r\n\r\nI tried \r\n\r\n    depends_on('boxlib+dims=3') # how do we say 3D boxlib?\r\n\r\nBut, that doesn't work. Spack reports...\r\n==> Error: Unexpected token\r\n",
